comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T15:37:42.471Z",maintainer-agent,"Evidence: ids.token_length settings section (default 4, bounds 4-12, validator-rejected outside range), generateItemId reads it with +6 escalation headroom, ids_token_length pm-config key (new integer max bound support), storage_integrity now reports validate_storage_duplicate_item_ids with per-id path lists + remediation hint. Manual sandbox: 6-char id minted (sbx-eum8uh), out-of-range 13 rejected, cross-folder duplicate detected as warning validate_storage_duplicate_item_ids:1. Collision math documented in MERGE_SAFETY.md. Specs: id-generation/settings-store/nested-settings/validate-command all green."
  "2026-07-19T16:09:08.025Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260719,"Acceptance and regression evidence: configurable id generation is exercised through create/copy/CLI registration/settings validation, with duplicate item IDs detected across type folders as a storage-integrity error. A packed-package install in a fresh temporary npm+git project configured a six-character token, created ac-e5d545, validated clean storage, then detected validate_storage_duplicate_item_ids after a cross-folder duplicate was introduced. Full suite: 317 files, 5,975 tests, 100/100/100/100 coverage."
  "2026-07-19T16:38:22.190Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260719,"Greptile pre-push review 2b371c5d-ceb0-4948-8d0a-1b403891b2c5 identified an escalation-bound asymmetry and implicit duplicate-path ordering. Accepted with corrections: ID generation now caps collision escalation at ID_TOKEN_LENGTH_MAX using Math.min (the bot's Math.max suggestion would not enforce the bound), a 12-character collision exhausts exactly 32 attempts without minting an out-of-contract ID, and duplicate path arrays sort explicitly at their owning contract boundary."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T15:38:34.402Z",maintainer-agent,"Local idExists probes cannot prevent cross-branch id collisions — only entropy (ids.token_length) shrinks the odds and only post-merge duplicate-id detection catches the residue. Birthday math for base36 tokens at 1% collision: len4 ~184 unsynced creations, len6 ~6.6k, len8 ~238k."
