body: "GH-600. Ids are prefix + 4 random base36 chars (~1.68M space); uniqueness enforced only via local on-disk idExists — blind to other branches and concurrent processes. Two agents branching from the same point can mint the same id for different items → silent identity collision surfacing as add/add merge conflict or ambiguous item. Same-disk sibling: pm-khdq (TOCTOU). Fix direction: entropy/length option or content-derived component + post-merge add/add collision detection in validate; document collision math per prefix length."
